    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-27T05:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-27T05:30:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–2753: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AGV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d785fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi, Cairo (for <persName corresp="#p_JJD1">Jernegan</persName>), and
                        London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-27T16:00:00+05:30"
                            >August 27, 1953—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. Re Karachi’s 172 August 26, repeated Delhi 43. While I fully appreciate
                    Karachi’s reaction to India’s attitude and actions re Kashmir, I wish to raise
                    question whether we are not in danger of becoming somewhat more involved with
                    this question than our national interests justify. It would be very serious
                    matter for US to get tied up militarily or become morally committed to assist
                    physically either side in territorial dispute so far from US shores. Many such
                    disputes exist around world, some of which we must learn to live with i.e.,
                    Trieste and Saar, helping where we can, through UN wherever possible, but
                    avoiding bilateral commitments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
